The Biden-Harris Administration is focused on combating human trafficking and has convened the President's Interagency Task Force to Monitor and Combat Trafficking in Persons (PITF). The PITF is responsible for coordinating efforts across 20 federal agencies and implementing the National Action Plan to Combat Human Trafficking. The plan focuses on prevention, protection, prosecution, and partnerships. The administration is committed to promoting gender and racial equity, advancing workers' rights, addressing forced labor in global supply chains, and ensuring safe migration. Human trafficking disproportionately affects marginalized communities. The fact sheet provides a summary of the administration's accomplishments in 2021 and plans for 2022.